metadata.name: 1939 Austin 7 Ulster
metadata.description: The Austin 7 is an economy car that was produced from 1922 until 1939 in the United Kingdom by Austin. It was at that time one of the most popular cars produced for the British market and sold well abroad. Its effect on the British market was similar to that of the Model T Ford in the US, replacing most other British economy cars and cyclecars of the early 1920s
